-- HSBC Equity Analysts Herrera, Galliano, Redman Leave Bank
-- B y   V e r o n i c a   N a v a r r o   E s p i n o s a
-- 2013-03-06T16:10:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-06/hsbc-equity-analysts-herrera-galliano-redman-leave-bank.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  equity analysts
Pedro Herrera,  Anisa Redman  and Victor Galliano have left the
bank, according to Juanita Gutierrez, a spokeswoman.  Mariel Santiago will lead Latin American financials
coverage from New York, Gutierrez said in an e-mail. Lauren Torres will cover Latin American food and beverages and
Alexandre Falcao will take over coverage of Latin American
agricultural businesses, according to Gutierrez.  The bank “will continue to add staff depending on business
needs to enhance overall emerging-market research,” Gutierrez
said.  Latin Finance had previously reported Galliano’s exit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Veronica Navarro Espinosa in New York at 
 vespinosa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
